 483        private void ProcessEvent(NetEvent evt)
 0484        {
 485            NetDebug.Write("[NM] Processing event: " + evt.Type);
 0486            bool emptyData = evt.DataReader.IsNull;
 0487            switch (evt.Type)
 488            {
 489                case NetEvent.EType.Connect:
 0490                    _netEventListener.OnPeerConnected(evt.Peer);
 0491                    break;
 492                case NetEvent.EType.Disconnect:
 0493                    var info = new DisconnectInfo
 494                    {
 495                        Reason = evt.DisconnectReason,
 496                        AdditionalData = evt.DataReader,
 497                        SocketErrorCode = evt.ErrorCode
 498                    };
 0499                    _netEventListener.OnPeerDisconnected(evt.Peer, info);
 0500                    RemovePeer(evt.Peer);
 0501                    break;
 502                case NetEvent.EType.Receive:
 0503                    _netEventListener.OnNetworkReceive(evt.Peer, evt.DataReader, evt.ChannelNumber, evt.DeliveryMethod);
 0504                    break;
 505                case NetEvent.EType.ReceiveUnconnected:
 0506                    _netEventListener.OnNetworkReceiveUnconnected(evt.RemoteEndPoint, evt.DataReader, UnconnectedMessage
 0507                    break;
 508                case NetEvent.EType.Broadcast:
 0509                    _netEventListener.OnNetworkReceiveUnconnected(evt.RemoteEndPoint, evt.DataReader, UnconnectedMessage
 0510                    break;
 511                case NetEvent.EType.Error:
 0512                    _netEventListener.OnNetworkError(evt.RemoteEndPoint, evt.ErrorCode);
 0513                    RemovePeer(evt.Peer);
 0514                    break;
 515                case NetEvent.EType.ConnectionLatencyUpdated:
 0516                    _netEventListener.OnNetworkLatencyUpdate(evt.Peer, evt.Latency);
 0517                    break;
 518                case NetEvent.EType.ConnectionRequest:
 0519                    _netEventListener.OnConnectionRequest(evt.ConnectionRequest);
 0520                    break;
 521                case NetEvent.EType.MessageDelivered:
 0522                    _deliveryEventListener.OnMessageDelivered(evt.Peer, evt.UserData);
 0523                    break;
 524                case NetEvent.EType.PeerAddressChanged:
 0525                    _peersLock.EnterUpgradeableReadLock();
 0526                    IPEndPoint previousAddress = null;
 0527                    if (ContainsPeer(evt.Peer))
 0528                    {
 0529                        _peersLock.EnterWriteLock();
 0530                        RemovePeerFromSet(evt.Peer);
 0531                        previousAddress = new(evt.Peer.Address, evt.Peer.Port);
 0532                        evt.Peer.FinishEndPointChange(evt.RemoteEndPoint);
 0533                        AddPeerToSet(evt.Peer);
 0534                        _peersLock.ExitWriteLock();
 0535                    }
 0536                    _peersLock.ExitUpgradeableReadLock();
 0537                    if (previousAddress != null && _peerAddressChangedListener != null)
 0538                        _peerAddressChangedListener.OnPeerAddressChanged(evt.Peer, previousAddress);
 0539                    break;
 540            }
 541            //Recycle if not message
 0542            if (emptyData)
 0543                RecycleEvent(evt);
 0544            else if (AutoRecycle)
 0545                evt.DataReader.RecycleInternal();
 0546        }

 561        //Update function
 562        private void UpdateLogic()
 0563        {
 0564            var peersToRemove = new List<NetPeer>();
 0565            var stopwatch = new Stopwatch();
 0566            stopwatch.Start();
 567
 0568            while (IsRunning)
 0569            {
 570                try
 0571                {
 0572                    ProcessDelayedPackets();
 0573                    int elapsed = (int)stopwatch.ElapsedMilliseconds;
 0574                    elapsed = elapsed <= 0 ? 1 : elapsed;
 0575                    stopwatch.Restart();
 576
 0577                    for (var netPeer = _headPeer; netPeer != null; netPeer = netPeer.NextPeer)
 0578                    {
 0579                        if (netPeer.ConnectionState == ConnectionState.Disconnected &&
 580                            netPeer.TimeSinceLastPacket > DisconnectTimeout)
 0581                        {
 0582                            peersToRemove.Add(netPeer);
 0583                        }

 0585                        {
 0586                            netPeer.Update(elapsed);
 0587                        }
 0588                    }

 0590                    if (peersToRemove.Count > 0)

 0593                        for (int i = 0; i < peersToRemove.Count; i++)
 0594                            RemovePeerInternal(peersToRemove[i]);
 0595                        _peersLock.ExitWriteLock();
 0596                        peersToRemove.Clear();
 0597                    }
 598
 0599                    ProcessNtpRequests(elapsed);
 600
 0601                    int sleepTime = UpdateTime - (int)stopwatch.ElapsedMilliseconds;
 0602                    if (sleepTime > 0)
 0603                        _updateTriggerEvent.WaitOne(sleepTime);
 0604                }
 0605                catch (ThreadAbortException)
 0606                {
 0607                    return;
 608                }
 0609                catch (Exception e)
 0610                {
 0611                    NetDebug.WriteError("[NM] LogicThread error: " + e);
 0612                }
 0613            }
 0614            stopwatch.Stop();
 0615        }

 687        internal NetPeer OnConnectionSolved(ConnectionRequest request, byte[] rejectData, int start, int length)
 0688        {
 0689            NetPeer netPeer = null;
 690
 0691            if (request.Result == ConnectionRequestResult.RejectForce)
 0692            {
 693                NetDebug.Write(NetLogLevel.Trace, "[NM] Peer connect reject force.");
 0694                if (rejectData != null && length > 0)
 0695                {
 0696                    var shutdownPacket = PoolGetWithProperty(PacketProperty.Disconnect, length);
 0697                    shutdownPacket.ConnectionNumber = request.InternalPacket.ConnectionNumber;
 0698                    FastBitConverter.GetBytes(shutdownPacket.RawData, 1, request.InternalPacket.ConnectionTime);
 0699                    if (shutdownPacket.Size >= NetConstants.PossibleMtu[0])
 0700                        NetDebug.WriteError("[Peer] Disconnect additional data size more than MTU!");
 701                    else
 0702                        Buffer.BlockCopy(rejectData, start, shutdownPacket.RawData, 9, length);
 0703                    SendRawAndRecycle(shutdownPacket, request.RemoteEndPoint);
 0704                }
 0705                lock (_requestsDict)
 0706                    _requestsDict.Remove(request.RemoteEndPoint);
 0707            }
 0708            else lock (_requestsDict)
 0709                {
 0710                    if (TryGetPeer(request.RemoteEndPoint, out netPeer))
 0711                    {
 712                        //already have peer
 0713                    }
 0714                    else if (request.Result == ConnectionRequestResult.Reject)
 0715                    {
 0716                        netPeer = new(this, request.RemoteEndPoint, GetNextPeerId());
 0717                        netPeer.Reject(request.InternalPacket, rejectData, start, length);
 0718                        AddPeer(netPeer);
 719                        NetDebug.Write(NetLogLevel.Trace, "[NM] Peer connect reject.");
 0720                    }
 721                    else //Accept
 0722                    {
 0723                        netPeer = new(this, request, GetNextPeerId());
 0724                        AddPeer(netPeer);
 0725                        CreateEvent(NetEvent.EType.Connect, netPeer);
 726                        NetDebug.Write(NetLogLevel.Trace, $"[NM] Received peer connection Id: {netPeer.ConnectTime}, EP:
 0727                    }
 0728                    _requestsDict.Remove(request.RemoteEndPoint);
 0729                }
 730
 0731            return netPeer;
 0732        }

 734        private int GetNextPeerId()
 0735        {
 736            /* Build a small queue so that when fetching
 737            * an id its unlikely to be one that was just returned. This adds
 738            * a buffer to applications which may be using the Id to identity
 739            * clients in their code, but may need time to dispose of objects
 740            * associated with the Id. */
 741            const int addCount = 5000;
 742            const int halfCount = (addCount / 2);
 0743            if (_peerIds.Count < halfCount)
 0744            {
 745                //At most how many can be added.
 746                const int maxIdValue = int.MaxValue;
 0747                long addable = Math.Min(addCount, (maxIdValue - _nextPeerId));
 748
 0749                if (addable == 0)
 0750                {
 751                    NetDebug.Write(NetLogLevel.Error, $"[NM] PeerIds have exceeded the maximum value of {maxIdValue}. A 
 0752                    return 0;
 753                }
 754
 0755                for (int i = 0; i < addCount; i++)
 0756                    _peerIds.Enqueue(_nextPeerId++);
 0757            }
 758
 0759            return (_peerIds.TryDequeue(out int result)) ? result : _nextPeerId++;
 0760        }

 762        private void ProcessConnectRequest(
 763            IPEndPoint remoteEndPoint,
 764            NetPeer netPeer,
 765            NetConnectRequestPacket connRequest)
 0766        {
 767            //if we have peer
 0768            if (netPeer != null)
 0769            {
 0770                var processResult = netPeer.ProcessConnectRequest(connRequest);

 772
 0773                switch (processResult)

 780                    case ConnectRequestResult.NewConnection:

 784                    case ConnectRequestResult.P2PLose:

 792                }
 793                //ConnectRequestResult.NewConnection

 0796                    connRequest.ConnectionNumber = (byte)((netPeer.ConnectionNum + 1) % NetConstants.MaxConnectionNumber

 0798            }
 799            else

 0802            }

 0808                {

 0810                    return;
 811                }
 0812                req = new(remoteEndPoint, connRequest, this);
 0813                _requestsDict.Add(remoteEndPoint, req);
 0814            }
 815            NetDebug.Write($"[NM] Creating request event: {connRequest.ConnectionTime}");

 0913                    {

 0915                        return;
 916                    }
 0917                    break;
 918                //unconnected messages
 919                case PacketProperty.Broadcast:
 0920                    if (!BroadcastReceiveEnabled)
 0921                        return;
 0922                    CreateEvent(NetEvent.EType.Broadcast, remoteEndPoint: remoteEndPoint, readerSource: packet);
 0923                    return;
 924                case PacketProperty.UnconnectedMessage:
 0925                    if (!UnconnectedMessagesEnabled)
 0926                        return;
 0927                    CreateEvent(NetEvent.EType.ReceiveUnconnected, remoteEndPoint: remoteEndPoint, readerSource: packet)
 0928                    return;
 929                case PacketProperty.NatMessage:
 0930                    if (NatPunchEnabled)
 0931                        NatPunchModule.ProcessMessage(remoteEndPoint, packet);
 0932                    return;
 933            }
 934

 0936            bool peerFound = remoteEndPoint is NetPeer netPeer || TryGetPeer(remoteEndPoint, out netPeer);

 0938            if (peerFound && EnableStatistics)

 945            {
 946                case PacketProperty.ConnectRequest:

 951                case PacketProperty.PeerNotFound:
 0952                    if (peerFound) //local
 0953                    {
 0954                        if (netPeer.ConnectionState != ConnectionState.Connected)
 0955                            return;
 0956                        if (packet.Size == 1)
 0957                        {
 958                            //first reply
 959                            //send NetworkChanged packet
 0960                            netPeer.ResetMtu();
 0961                            SendRaw(NetConnectAcceptPacket.MakeNetworkChanged(netPeer), remoteEndPoint);
 962                            NetDebug.Write($"PeerNotFound sending connection info: {remoteEndPoint}");
 0963                        }
 0964                        else if (packet.Size == 2 && packet.RawData[1] == 1)
 0965                        {
 966                            //second reply
 0967                            DisconnectPeerForce(netPeer, DisconnectReason.PeerNotFound, 0, null);
 0968                        }
 0969                    }
 0970                    else if (packet.Size > 1) //remote
 0971                    {
 972                        //check if this is old peer
 0973                        bool isOldPeer = false;
 974
 0975                        if (AllowPeerAddressChange)
 0976                        {
 977                            NetDebug.Write($"[NM] Looks like address change: {packet.Size}");
 0978                            var remoteData = NetConnectAcceptPacket.FromData(packet);
 0979                            if (remoteData != null &&
 980                                remoteData.PeerNetworkChanged &&
 981                                remoteData.PeerId < _peersArray.Length)
 0982                            {
 0983                                _peersLock.EnterUpgradeableReadLock();

 0985                                _peersLock.ExitUpgradeableReadLock();

 987                                    peer.ConnectTime == remoteData.ConnectionTime &&
 988                                    peer.ConnectionNum == remoteData.ConnectionNumber)
 0989                                {
 0990                                    if (peer.ConnectionState == ConnectionState.Connected)
 0991                                    {
 0992                                        peer.InitiateEndPointChange();
 0993                                        CreateEvent(NetEvent.EType.PeerAddressChanged, peer, remoteEndPoint);
 994                                        NetDebug.Write("[NM] PeerNotFound change address of remote peer");
 0995                                    }
 0996                                    isOldPeer = true;
 0997                                }
 0998                            }
 0999                        }

 01001                        PoolRecycle(packet);
 1002
 1003                        //else peer really not found
 01004                        if (!isOldPeer)
 01005                        {
 01006                            var secondResponse = PoolGetWithProperty(PacketProperty.PeerNotFound, 1);
 01007                            secondResponse.RawData[1] = 1;
 01008                            SendRawAndRecycle(secondResponse, remoteEndPoint);
 01009                        }
 01010                    }
 01011                    break;
 1012                case PacketProperty.InvalidProtocol:
 01013                    if (peerFound && netPeer.ConnectionState == ConnectionState.Outgoing)
 01014                        DisconnectPeerForce(netPeer, DisconnectReason.InvalidProtocol, 0, null);
 01015                    break;
 1016                case PacketProperty.Disconnect:
 01017                    if (peerFound)
 01018                    {
 01019                        var disconnectResult = netPeer.ProcessDisconnect(packet);
 01020                        if (disconnectResult == DisconnectResult.None)
 01021                        {
 01022                            PoolRecycle(packet);
 01023                            return;
 1024                        }
 01025                        DisconnectPeerForce(
 1026                            netPeer,
 1027                            disconnectResult == DisconnectResult.Disconnect
 1028                            ? DisconnectReason.RemoteConnectionClose
 1029                            : DisconnectReason.ConnectionRejected,
 1030                            0, packet);
 01031                    }
 1032                    else
 01033                    {
 01034                        PoolRecycle(packet);
 01035                    }
 1036                    //Send shutdown
 01037                    SendRawAndRecycle(PoolGetWithProperty(PacketProperty.ShutdownOk), remoteEndPoint);
 01038                    break;
 1039                case PacketProperty.ConnectAccept:
 01040                    if (!peerFound)
 01041                        return;
 01042                    var connAccept = NetConnectAcceptPacket.FromData(packet);
 01043                    if (connAccept != null && netPeer.ProcessConnectAccept(connAccept))
 01044                        CreateEvent(NetEvent.EType.Connect, netPeer);
 01045                    break;
 1046                default:
 01047                    if (peerFound)
 01048                        netPeer.ProcessPacket(packet);
 1049                    else
 01050                        SendRawAndRecycle(PoolGetWithProperty(PacketProperty.PeerNotFound), remoteEndPoint);
 01051                    break;
 1052            }
 01053        }

 1470        /// <summary>
 1471        /// Receive "maxProcessedEvents" pending events. Call this in game update code
 1472        /// In Manual mode it will call also socket Receive (which can be slow)
 1473        /// 0 - receive all events
 1474        /// </summary>
 1475        /// <param name="maxProcessedEvents">Max events that will be processed (called INetEventListener Connect/Receive
 1476        public void PollEvents(int maxProcessedEvents = 0)
 01477        {
 01478            if (_manualMode)
 01479            {
 01480                if (_udpSocketv4 != null)
 01481                    ManualReceive(_udpSocketv4, _bufferEndPointv4, maxProcessedEvents);
 01482                if (_udpSocketv6 != null && _udpSocketv6 != _udpSocketv4)
 01483                    ManualReceive(_udpSocketv6, _bufferEndPointv6, maxProcessedEvents);
 01484                ProcessDelayedPackets();
 01485                return;
 1486            }
 01487            if (UnsyncedEvents)
 01488                return;
 1489            NetEvent pendingEvent;
 01490            lock (_eventLock)
 01491            {
 01492                pendingEvent = _pendingEventHead;
 01493                _pendingEventHead = null;
 01494                _pendingEventTail = null;
 01495            }
 1496
 01497            int counter = 0;
 01498            while (pendingEvent != null)
 01499            {
 01500                var next = pendingEvent.Next;
 01501                ProcessEvent(pendingEvent);
 01502                pendingEvent = next;
 01503                counter++;
 01504                if (counter == maxProcessedEvents)
 01505                    break;
 01506            }
 01507        }

 1557        /// <summary>
 1558        /// Connect to remote host
 1559        /// </summary>
 1560        /// <param name="target">Server end point (ip and port)</param>
 1561        /// <param name="connectionData">Additional data for remote peer</param>
 1562        /// <returns>New NetPeer if new connection, Old NetPeer if already connected, null peer if there is ConnectionRe
 1563        /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">Manager is not running. Call <see cref="Start()"/></exception>
 1564        public NetPeer Connect(IPEndPoint target, NetDataWriter connectionData)
 01565        {
 01566            if (!IsRunning)
 01567                throw new InvalidOperationException("Client is not running");
 1568
 01569            lock (_requestsDict)
 01570            {
 01571                if (_requestsDict.ContainsKey(target))
 01572                    return null;
 1573
 01574                byte connectionNumber = 0;
 01575                if (TryGetPeer(target, out var peer))
 01576                {
 01577                    switch (peer.ConnectionState)
 1578                    {
 1579                        //just return already connected peer
 1580                        case ConnectionState.Connected:
 1581                        case ConnectionState.Outgoing:
 01582                            return peer;
 1583                    }
 1584                    //else reconnect
 01585                    connectionNumber = (byte)((peer.ConnectionNum + 1) % NetConstants.MaxConnectionNumber);
 01586                    RemovePeer(peer);
 01587                }
 1588
 1589                //Create reliable connection
 1590                //And send connection request
 01591                peer = new(this, target, GetNextPeerId(), connectionNumber, connectionData);
 01592                AddPeer(peer);
 01593                return peer;
 1594            }
 01595        }
